Per-test coverage (loader.test.ts):
  extractHost
    ✓ strips a leading www.        ("https://www.linkedin.com/in/foo" → "linkedin.com")
    ✓ leaves bare apex alone       ("https://linkedin.com/"           → "linkedin.com")
    ✓ does NOT strip non-www subdomains   ("https://jira.acme.com/..." → "jira.acme.com")
    ✓ lowercases the host          ("https://LinkedIn.COM/"           → "linkedin.com")
    ✓ strips a trailing dot        ("https://linkedin.com./"          → "linkedin.com")
    ✓ throws on garbage            ("not a url"                       → TypeError)
  loadStorageStateForUrl
    ✓ returns null when no row matches (SELECT runs, returns [])
    ✓ returns the row when one matches (www stripped from URL host)
    ✓ returns null and never throws on an unparseable URL (no DB call)
    ✓ returns null and swallows a SELECT failure (logs, returns null)
  markBrowserSiteVerified
    ✓ UPDATEs last_verified_at for the host
    ✓ swallows UPDATE failure (best-effort, never throws)

Verify contract per §E.2:
  ✓ URL → host extraction
  ✓ loader returns null when no row exists
  ✓ loader returns storage state when matching row exists
  ✓ markBrowserSiteVerified updates last_verified_at
  ✓ worker vitest green for loader.test.ts
  ✓ worker tsc clean

Out-of-scope per spec (handled in E.3):
  - Sign-in wall detection / browser_login_required event — separate file
    worker/src/browser-sites/detector.ts ships in E.3.
  - Real cookie + localStorage application to the Browserbase session.
    The plan flags this as harness-daemon work; until then E.2 emits a
    `browser_session_storage_state_not_supported` activity event so live
    e2e can confirm the loader pipeline is wired even though bytes
    aren't yet getting applied to the page.
  - markBrowserSiteVerified call-site in goto_url is intentionally
    deferred to E.3 (it depends on detectSignInWall returning negative
    on the first navigation to be a meaningful "verified" signal).

Notes:
  - browserSites uses the same `quotaSql` postgres connection
    (max:2, idle_timeout:60) that the quota gate uses, since SELECTs
    are short-lived and the read pattern is identical.
  - The host CHECK constraint from E.1 (^[a-z0-9.-]+$) is enforced
    DB-side; the loader doesn't re-validate before SELECT because
    parameter binding via postgres-js prevents injection regardless.
